 In the forest maze of Super Mario RPG, 

00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:35.460
 Mario experiences a different kind of pipe. 

00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:40.040
 Log pipes - they function very similarly to the normal green version. 

00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:45.280
 Surprisingly, we start looking abroad again for a real world example. 

00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:47.720
 Because maybe already in the 13th century, 

00:05:47.720 --> 00:05:52.040
 people in England used hollowed tree trunks for water pipelines. 

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:54.720
 In the end the Americans took over the idea, 

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:57.600
 and installed wooden pipes in the early 1800s 

00:05:57.600 --> 00:05:59.640
 [NOW YOU KNOW IT...] 

00:05:59.640 --> 00:06:02.300
 And now it's time for my last thought. 

00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:05.760
 We grew up believing what Nintendo has always told us, 

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:10.920
 that Mario is a true Italian-American thoroughbred from New York who lives in the Mushroom Kingdom! 

00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:14.920
 But what we have seen here today could point in a different direction. 

00:06:14.920 --> 00:06:17.940
 We learned that crabs run in the sewers of Italy, 

00:06:17.940 --> 00:06:23.100
 and that turtles have a better chance of survival in sewer conditions with warmer climates. 

00:06:23.100 --> 00:06:27.860
 Now we know that a leading green pipeline manufacturer has a headquarters in Germany, 

00:06:27.860 --> 00:06:31.280
 and that stone pipelines and agricultural systems 

00:06:31.280 --> 00:06:34.360
 can usually be found in old European cities 

00:06:34.360 --> 00:06:36.060
 So what does this tell us? 

00:06:36.060 --> 00:06:37.240
 Only this: 

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:44.760
 That our Italian - '' American '' unblocker actually has fewer American connections than we thought 

00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:49.940
 and that - perhaps - the Mushroom Kingdom can actually be found in the Old Continent. 

